def: Power, or command, over a certain district; chieftainship.[Obs.]
Whisky; especially, whisky illicitly distilled by the Irishpeasantry. [Written also potheen, and potteen.]
A square sail bent upon a yard that hangs obliquely to the mastand is raised or lowered with the sail. Totten.
Like, or pertaining to, the crocodile; characteristic of thecrocodile.-- n.
The act of sustaining; maintenance; support. Milton. Lowell.
One who goes upon an expedition. [R].
Disposed; inclined; having a mind.Joseph... was minded to put her away privily. Matt. i. 19.If men were minded to live virtuously. Tillotson.
